---
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Opening quote as typography hero -->
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <p class="font-quote text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-text-deep leading-[1.2] italic">
          "Margin is the space between our load and our limits."
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-text-muted tracking-wide uppercase font-semibold">
          Richard Swenson
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Divider -->
      <div class="my-16 flex justify-center reveal">
        <div class="w-16 h-px bg-text-faint/30"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Body copy: asymmetric editorial grid -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-5 reveal">
          <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">
            The concept
          </p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05]">
            The space between your life and your limits.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <p>
            Applied to finances, margin is the gap between what you earn and what you spend. It's the cushion that absorbs life's surprises. It's the reserve that lets you breathe.
          </p>
          <p>
            Margin isn't about having less. It's about having space.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Contrast cards -->
      <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="p-8 bg-warm-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-text-faint">
            Living at the edge
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Every dollar accounted for. Every expense justified. Any surprise becomes a crisis. Generosity feels impossible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-8 bg-storehouse-50 rounded-2xl border border-storehouse-200/60">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-storehouse-700">
            Living with margin
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-body leading-relaxed">
            Room to respond. Space to give. Capacity for the unexpected. Peace instead of panic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
